* ngspice init for ANN_Kicad simulation
* Both vendor models (Microchip MCP6001, TI LM2901/LM339) are PSpice-syntax:
* they use POLY() and PSpice-style TABLE {expr} ((x,y)(x,y)) constructs that
* ngspice only accepts in PSpice compatibility mode.
set ngbehavior=ps
* NOTE: gmin cannot be set here (ngspice rejects it before a circuit is loaded).
* Microchip's model header recommends GMIN=100f for high-impedance circuits;
* that is applied per-deck via ".options gmin=100f" instead.
